actions.text: Referred to Senate Committee on Judiciary.

official_title: A joint resolution proposing an amendment to the Constitution of the United States with respect to the minimum age qualifications of Representatives and Senators.

summary.text: Constitutional Amendment - Reduces the minimum age qualification for a Representative to twenty-two years. Reduces the minimum age qualification for a Senator to twenty-seven years.

titles.title: A joint resolution proposing an amendment to the Constitution of the United States with respect to the minimum age qualifications of Representatives and Senators.
